<p>To find or register for online courses:</p>
<ol start="1">
<li>Log-in through <a href="https://web.byui.edu/services/login?RedirectURL=https://my.byui.edu" target="_blank">my.byui.edu</a></li>
<li>Click on the blue "<strong>STUDENT</strong>" tab</li>
<li>Click on the "<strong>Course Search</strong>" icon in the Registration box on the bottom left side of the page</li>
<li>Complete the following fields:
<ul>
<li><strong>Term</strong>: Choose desired term (Ex: Spring Semester 2012)</li>
<li><strong>Sub Program:</strong> ACST (Academic Start)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>This should give you a listing of online courses being offered that semester.</li>
<li>To add a course, click the "Add" checkbox next to the desired&nbsp;course and section;&nbsp;then click the "Add Courses" button at the bottom of the page. The "Add" box will not be available until your <a href="http://www.byui.edu/registrarsoffice/RegSchedule.htm">registration period</a> opens.</li>
</ol>
<p><iframe frameborder="0" height="469" src="http://player.vimeo.com/video/43935309" width="500"></iframe></p>
<p><a href="http://vimeo.com/43935309">Pathway Registration Tutorial</a> from <a href="http://vimeo.com/user12112672">Todd Cardon</a> on <a href="http://vimeo.com">Vimeo</a>.</p>
